  "body": "After registering my initial account on the stable release Mac desktop client, I was given my 12 word recovery key, which I screengrabbed and kept in a safe place.\r\n\r\nAfter trying to recover my account with my 12 word key, the desktop client actually created a new account altogether with a new contact code.\r\n\r\nI tried again, and the same thing happened - 2 new accounts with new contact codes, for both times I tried to recover my initial account.\r\n\r\nAfter chatting with Corey, I downloaded the nightly build of the desktop client, and again went through the account recovery, **with my initial recovery phrase**, and it recovered one of the new accounts the desktop client created.  I tried my recovery phrase on the mobile app (iOS), and it again recovered the same (newer) account that the nightly desktop build recovered.\r\n\r\n@corpetty ",
